The "number" property types are converted to javascript numbers before being passed to the underlying graphing engine. The definition objects declared by the engines accept the following settings:

|!Setting |!Description |
|>|[[settings allowed by all properties|Property Types]] |
|increment |Sets step value of the range slider. Should be positive. (default: <<.value 1>>) |
|min |Sets the minimum allowed value in the range slider (default: <<.value 0>>) |
|max |Sets the maximum allowed value in the range slider (default: <<.value "min + increment * 100">>) |

The settings only affect how the number slider is configured in property configuration tables. min and max does not constrain values if users write in.
